        <h1>📚 Review Week Assignment</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">Independent Bible Study Practice</p>

        <div class="purpose-box">
            <h2>📖 Purpose</h2>
            <p>This week is for independent Bible study. Each person has been assigned a specific week from our previous lessons. Your task is to review that week's content, answer the questions using Scripture, and be prepared to share what you learned when we meet again.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="instructions">
            <h3>✅ How This Works:</h3>
            <ol>
                <li><strong>Find your assigned week below</strong> - Each person has one specific week</li>
                <li><strong>Click the checkbox next to your name</strong> - This opens your personal notes section</li>
                <li><strong>Fill in your answers</strong> - Type directly into the note fields (they auto-save!)</li>
                <li><strong>When done, click "Email My Notes"</strong> - This opens your email app with your notes ready to send to yourself</li>
                <li><strong>Bring your notes to the next meeting</strong> - You'll share what you learned (3-5 minutes)</li>
            </ol>

            <div class="tips">
                <strong>💡 Tips for Success:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Your notes automatically save as you type - no need to click save repeatedly</li>
                    <li>Use the "Email My Notes" button to send them to yourself - easiest way to keep them!</li>
                    <li>If you prefer, you can also "Download as File" to save to your phone</li>
                    <li>Want to do extra? Feel free to work on other weeks too!</li>
                    <li>Access the original study guides at: <a href="https://jagsjim.github.io/small_group/" style="color: #0d47a1;">jagsjim.github.io/small_group</a></li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="bible-note">
                📖 Remember: Use your Bible! The study guides help understanding, but always quote Scripture itself in your answers.
            </div>
        </div>

